---
description: Deckle PDF generation SDK usage guidance — imports, initialization, generate/template calls, response shape, formats, free-tier limits, and security notes.
alwaysApply: false
---

When using Deckle for PDF generation:
- Import: import { Deckle } from 'deckle'
- Initialize with API key: const df = new Deckle(process.env.DECKLE_API_KEY)
- Generate from HTML: await df.generate({ html: '...', options: { format: 'A4' } })
- Generate from template: await df.fromTemplate({ template: 'tmpl_xxx', data: { ... } })
- Response includes: id, status, url, pages, file_size, generation_time_ms
- Supported formats: A4, Letter, Legal, or custom { width, height }
- Headers/footers support {{pageNumber}} and {{totalPages}} interpolation
- Free tier: 1,000 PDFs/month
- Always use server-side API calls — never expose the API key in client-side code
- For Next.js: create an API route that calls Deckle, then call that route from the client
- For Express: create an endpoint that generates the PDF and returns the URL
- Python SDK: from deckle import Deckle; df = Deckle("dk_live_...")
- Template syntax uses Handlebars: {{variable}}, {{#each items}}, {{#if condition}}
